  "prompt": "Up to what rank in GATE ECE can we expect a call from BARC for an interview?",
  "response": "The rank at which you can expect a call from BARC (Bhabha Atomic Research Centre) for an interview through the GATE (Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering) exam can vary each year based on several factors, such as the number of applicants, the difficulty level of the exam, and specific requirements for the position.\n\nIn recent years, candidates with a GATE rank within the top 400-600 for the Electronics and Communication Engineering (ECE) stream have been known to receive interview calls from BARC. However, this is just a general guideline and can change based on the above-mentioned factors. It is advisable to check the official BARC recruitment notifications for the most accurate and updated information regarding the selection criteria and cutoff ranks for the current year.",
